commentPostTextItems.html: And its all over, Zim have lost by huge margin of 148 runs, the batsman let them down today, carlisle played well for his 31 and there have been no others except for the pinch hitter Strang
Please join us again tomorrow for the final ODI, zimbabwe need to win in order to consider this anot a total white wash
Match State: SA won by 148 runs

In the presentations, Guy Whittall said the toss had nothing to do with it, as they would have fielded anyway, tomorrow they may keep the same side, but may bring in another spinner. Pollock said the batting wasn't easy and the bowlers played well

The Man of the match is J Rhodes, who fielded well and had a super knock of 56 off 45 balls as well as a catch and good fielding, he said he enjoyed all of it and didn't find the batting that hard as the pitch played his style
